<inglise> Regulation (EEC) No 1728/74 of the Council of 27 June 1974 on the coordination of agricultural research </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 1728/74 p&otilde;llumajandusuuringute koosk&otilde;lastamise kohta 27. juuni 1974 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community and in particular Article 43 thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 43, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Opinion of the European Parliament; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas effective coordination of research in agriculture should have as its aim the best possible organization, in the general interest, of the efforts made in the Member States, effective use of the results of these efforts, orientation of them in such a way that they are consistent with the needs of the common agricultural policy, and the pooling of research facilities with a view to studying certain problems of particular importance to the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: p&otilde;llumajandusuuringute t&otilde;husa koosk&otilde;lastamise eesm&auml;rk peaks olema liikmesriikide j&otilde;upingutuste parim v&otilde;imalik rakendamine &uuml;ldistes huvides, nende j&otilde;upingutuste tulemuste t&otilde;hus kasutamine, nende suunamine nii, et need oleksid &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika suhtes j&auml;rjepidevad, ja uurimisv&otilde;imaluste &uuml;hine kasutamine, et uurida teatavaid &uuml;hendusele eriti t&auml;htsaid probleeme; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in order to achieve this aim, it is necessary to make provision for exchanges of information and reciprocal consultation on the programmes of agricultural research already existing or envisaged in the Member States; </inglise>
<eesti> selle eesm&auml;rgi saavutamiseks on vaja ette n&auml;ha liikmesriikides juba teostatavaid v&otilde;i kavandatavaid p&otilde;llumajandusuuringuprogramme k&auml;sitlev teabevahetus ja vastastikune n&otilde;upidamine liikmesriikide vahel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in a certain number of cases the desired objective may be attained through coordination at Community level of certain national research projects; </inglise>
<eesti> teatavatel juhtudel v&otilde;ib soovitud eesm&auml;rgi saavutada teatavate siseriiklike uurimist&ouml;&ouml;de koosk&otilde;lastamise teel &uuml;henduse tasandil; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, however, these measures may appear insufficient either because of their nature, or because the means available to the Member States do not allow them to increase their research efforts in such a way as to fulfil the requirements of the common agricultural policy entirely; whereas in these cases, the Community should be able to support and supplement the efforts made in the Member States in order to meet research requirements more effectively and to fulfil the needs of the common agricultural policy; </inglise>
<eesti> need meetmed v&otilde;ivad siiski osutuda ebapiisavateks oma laadi t&otilde;ttu v&otilde;i seet&otilde;ttu, et liikmesriikide k&auml;sutuses olevad vahendid ei v&otilde;imalda neil suurendada oma j&otilde;upingutusi uurimist&ouml;&ouml;de alal nii, et t&auml;ielikult t&auml;ita &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika n&otilde;udeid; sel juhul peaks &uuml;hendus saama toetada ja t&auml;iendada liikmesriikide j&otilde;upingutusi, et t&auml;ita uurimisalaseid n&otilde;udeid paremini ja rahuldada &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika vajadusi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas since the coordination of agricultural research is closely linked to the common agricultural policy, and since, as a result, efforts are concentrated especially on coordinating applied research, the earliest possible utilization by farmers of the results of this research must be ensured; </inglise>
<eesti> kuna p&otilde;llumajandusuuringute koosk&otilde;lastamine on tihedalt seotud &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitikaga ja seet&otilde;ttu keskenduvad j&otilde;upingutused eelk&otilde;ige rakendusuuringute koosk&otilde;lastamisele, tuleb tagada, et p&otilde;llumajandustootjad kasutavad selle uurimist&ouml;&ouml; tulemusi v&otilde;imalikult kiiresti; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, because of the needs of coordination and as a result of the complexity of the scientific problems to be studied and the projects to be implemented, direct and continuous cooperation between the Commission and the Member States is desirable; </inglise>
<eesti> koosk&otilde;lastamisvajaduste t&otilde;ttu ning uuritavate teaduslike probleemide ja teostatavate projektide keerukuse t&otilde;ttu on soovitav vahetu ja pidev koost&ouml;&ouml; komisjoni ja liikmesriikide vahel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas within the framework of the general policy in the field of science and technology worked out by the Commission with the help of the relevant consultative bodies, the most appropriate way of developing cooperation is to set up a Committee consisting of representatives of the Member States and presided over by a representative of the Commission which could usefully help and advise the Commission in carrying out the tasks which devolve upon it in the field of the coordination of research in agriculture; </inglise>
<eesti> sobivaim viis koost&ouml;&ouml; arendamiseks teadust ja tehnoloogiat k&auml;sitlevate &uuml;ldp&otilde;him&otilde;tete raames, mille komisjon on v&auml;lja t&ouml;&ouml;tanud asjakohaste n&otilde;uandeorganite abiga, on asutada liikmesriikide esindajatest koosnev komitee, mille eesistujaks on komisjoni esindaja ning mis v&otilde;iks t&otilde;husalt aidata ja n&otilde;ustada komisjoni talle p&otilde;llumajandusuuringute koosk&otilde;lastamise vallas pandud &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the coordination of national efforts demands a thorough knowledge of the situation in each Member State so far as agricultural research is concerned as well as sufficient information on other research relevant to agriculture; whereas it is necessary to determine the procedure whereby the data so obtained will be made available to the users; </inglise>
<eesti> siseriiklike j&otilde;upingutuste koosk&otilde;lastamiseks on vaja nii p&otilde;hjalikke teadmisi iga liikmesriigi olukorrast p&otilde;llumajandusuuringute vallas kui ka piisavat teavet muude p&otilde;llumajandusega seotud uurimist&ouml;&ouml;de kohta; on vaja kinnitada sel viisil saadud andmete kasutajatele k&auml;ttesaadavaks muutmise kord; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas care must be taken to put the results of research in which the Community takes part at the disposal of the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleb hoolitseda selle eest, et nende uurimist&ouml;&ouml;de tulemused, milles &uuml;hendus osaleb, antakse &uuml;henduse k&auml;sutusse; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in order to ensure practical application of the results obtained, it is necessary to promote the publication and dissemination of the results, </inglise>
<eesti> saadud tulemuste tegeliku rakendamise tagamiseks on vaja edendada nende avaldamist ja levitamist, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> In order to further the attainment of the aims of the common agricultural policy, coordination and promotion at Community level of agricultural research activities undertaken in the Member States shall take place in accordance with the provisions laid down in this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika eesm&auml;rkide paremaks saavutamiseks koosk&otilde;lastatakse liikmesriikide j&otilde;upingutused p&otilde;llumajandusuuringute vallas ja edendatakse neid &uuml;henduse tasandil koosk&otilde;las k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatuga. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> In applying this Regulation account shall be taken, in a suitable manner, of the general scientific and technological policy laid down by the Community's institutions. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaldamisel v&otilde;etakse sobival viisil arvesse teaduse ja tehnoloogia vallas &uuml;henduse institutsioonide kehtestatud &uuml;ldp&otilde;him&otilde;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise> TITLE I </inglise>
